            <thetext>Currently there is no such thing similar to
  &quot;qx.ui.table.selection.Model.NO_SELECTION&quot;
for qx.ui.list.List selection models.

The property qx.ui.list.List#selectionMode only allows these values:
  [&quot;single&quot;, &quot;multi&quot;, &quot;additive&quot;, &quot;one&quot;]
and setting it to &lt;null&gt; did not work either.

An additional value &quot;none&quot; should be added for the selectionMode.
Setting the selectionMode to &quot;none&quot; should render the lists items
&#39;unselectable&#39; (a.k.a. readOnly)

This applies to qooxdoo version 2.1.x and 3.0.x</thetext>
